The paper deals with image processing and computer vision, specifically the problem of salt-and-pepper noise removal using robust principal component analysis (RPCA) and dual weighted lp-norm (DWLP) models. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves optimization techniques and signal processing, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). The use of DWLP and its comparison with other state-of-the-art methods suggests a focus on machine learning and data analysis, which could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
